VPN Gateways are widely used in real-world enterprise environments.

For example, a multinational company connects its headquarters and branch offices to Azure using Site-to-Site VPN.

A real-life use case is secure remote access for employees working from home.

Another example is connecting on-premise databases to cloud-based applications.

Organizations also use VPN Gateways for disaster recovery, ensuring backup systems in Azure remain accessible.

These implementations provide secure, reliable, and scalable connectivity.
